---
import "../styles/global.css";
import { ClientRouter } from "astro:transitions";
import Carousel from "../components/Carousel";
import Icon from "../components/Icon.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Astro</title>
    <ClientRouter />
  </head>
  <body class="flex flex-col">
    <header class="flex justify-between px-6 py-4 items-center sticky top-0 bg-white z-10">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <img src="/habitat-wordmark.svg" />
      </div>
      <nav class="flex text-lg gap-8">
        <a href="/users">For users</a>
        <a href="/developers">For developers</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="flex-1 flex justify-end gap-4 items-center">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/habitat-network/habitat"
          aria-label="GitHub"
        >
          <Icon name="github" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/habitat.network" aria-label="Bluesky">
          <Icon name="bluesky" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://habitat.leaflet.pub" aria-label="Leaflet">
          <Icon name="leaflet" class="w-6 h-6" />
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section id="section-1" class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-6 gap-16 py-16">
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center">
          <div class="flex-1 overflow-visible">
            <div class="rounded-r-3xl overflow-hidden -ml-6">
              <img
                src="/robert-katzki-KLcaQxlmhtk-unsplash.jpg"
                class="max-h-150 w-full object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="prose px-12 my-8">
            <h1>We're building <b>user data agency</b> for the web.</h1>
            <p>
              Over the last decade, we've collectively
              experienced the internet get meaningfully... worse. Whether
              because of the attention economy, surveillance capitalism,
              enshittification, (or all the above and more), it's clear that the
              state of the web today isn't meant for us, for people. At the core
              of these issues lies data capture, through which Big Tech, data
              brokers, and surveillance dragnets have used our data against us. 
			  That's why to build a better web, we're trying
              to bring about user data ownership and agency at a protocol level.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="prose max-w-[90vw]">
        </div>
        <button
          onclick="document.getElementById('section-2').scrollIntoView({behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start'})"
          aria-label="Scroll to next section"
          class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-8 h-8" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <section id="section-2" class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-6 gap-16 py-16">
        <div class="prose">
          <h2>How does it work?</h2>
          <p>
            habitat provides a place where all your data lives and can be
            controlled by you. Developers build frontend apps, no third-party
            servers involved, so you can interact with that data how you
            normally would, but without sharing it with any other parties, keeping it safe from extraction and spying. This is
            all built on ATProtocol, a new open protocol for the social
            internet.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex">
          <div class="flex-1 py-8 flex flex-col gap-4 prose pr-6">
            <h3>The old way</h3>
            <img src="/traditional-way.png" alt="Traditional way" class="w-11/12" />
            <p>
              Traditional apps own the data you create with the app, and in order
              to share data with your friends they need to use the same app. This
              has enabled monopolies to build data moats that stifle competition
              while offering inferior experiences to users.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 py-8 flex flex-col gap-4 prose pl-6">
            <h3>The habitat way</h3>
            <img src="/habitat-way.png" alt="Traditional way" />
            <p>
              With habitat, you own your data and apps run locally on your device.
              Data is shared directly without involving third parties that can
              accumulate it. Apps are built to be compatible such that innovative
              user experiences can leverage existing data.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button
          onclick="document.getElementById('section-3').scrollIntoView({behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start'})"
          aria-label="Scroll to next section"
          class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-8 h-8" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <section id="section-3" class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-6 gap-16 py-16">
        <div class="prose">
          <h2>
            Big Tech continues to harvest and steal our data.
          </h2>
		            <h3>We're actually doing something about it. </h3> 
        </div>
        <div class="not-prose">
          <Carousel
            client:load
            items={[
              { image: "/google.png", alt: "Google" },
              { image: "/grammarly.png", alt: "Grammarly" },
              { image: "/ring.png", alt: "Ring" },
			                { image: "/ibm.png", alt: "IBM" },
			                { image: "/meta.png", alt: "Meta" },

            ]}
          />
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
		   <p>
            We believe your data should be yours, forever. Companies shouldn't be
            able to prevent you from accessing it and downloading it. Your data
            shouldn't flow through third-party servers just so you can share it with
            friends. We are laying the technical foundations to make this the new
            default on the web, so we can break free from the cycle of data
            capture that currently exists online.
          </p>
		  <h3>Sign up for the waitlist now.</h3>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
